cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.MM

This paper explores the relationship between social media activities and e-commerce platform activities, which involves topics related to social media analysis, information retrieval, and social computing. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning algorithms to predict e-commerce platform activities, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and social computing (cs.SOC).
